'''梅爾檸檬'''（學名：{{lang|la|''Citrus meyerii''}}），又名：'''北京柠檬'''、'''迈尔柠檬'''、'''迈耶柠檬'''、'''野柠檬'''、'''中国柠檬'''，是一种原产自[[中华人民共和国|中国]]的杂交[[柑橘属|柑橘属]]水果。不同于寻常柠檬和苦柠檬，这是[[枸櫞|枸櫞]]与[[橘|橘]]/[[柚|柚]]的杂交品种。<ref name="limes and lemons">{{cite journal | title=Phylogenetic origin of limes and lemons revealed by cytoplasmic and nuclear markers | last1=Curk | first1=Franck | last2=Ollitrault | first2= Frédérique | last3=Garcia-Lor | first3= Andres | last4=Luro | first4=François | last5=Navarro | first5=Luis | last6=Ollitrault | first6=Patrick | journal=Annals of Botany | volume=11 | issue=4 | pages=565–583 | year=2016 | doi=10.1093/aob/mcw005 | pmid=26944784 | pmc=4817432 }}</ref>

成龄树高约{{convert|6|to|10|ft|m|0|abbr=on}}，叶片深绿色带有光泽。花朵香气扑鼻，自内往外为紫色和白色。果实比[[柠檬|纯正的柠檬]]更圆，成熟时呈深黄色，略带橙色调，并且口感较甜，低酸。这种柠檬的高酸性ph值介于在2和3之间，汁水酸性比纯水高至一万至十万倍。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Lemon Juice: Acidic or Alkaline, and Does It Matter?|url=https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/lemon-juice-acidic-or-alkaline|website=Healthline|language=en|access-date=2020-05-06|archive-date=2021-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112065237/https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/lemon-juice-acidic-or-alkaline|dead-url=no}}</ref>这种酸度水平可以将其用作消毒清洁剂。

植物猎人{{tsl|en|Frank Nicholas Meyer|弗兰克·尼古拉斯·迈耶|弗兰克·尼古拉斯·迈耶}}，被[[美国农业部|美国农业部]]派遣至亚洲收集新的植物物种，随后在中国本土发现了该柠檬品种。<ref name="npr">{{cite news |title=The Meyer Lemon: More Than A Pretty Face |first=Julie |last=O'Hara |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=100778147&ft=1&f=1053 |quote=For more than a century, the Meyer lemon was known mostly for its looks. In its native China, it was primarily a decorative houseplant. The Meyer lemon might still be decorating homes today if it weren't for one man. In the early 1900s, the U.S. Department of Agriculture sent Frank N. Meyer, an agricultural explorer (yes, that was his actual job title) on several trips to Asia with the mission of collecting new plant species. Among more than 2,500 plants that he introduced to the U.S., the Meyer lemon was named in his honor. Sadly, Meyer would never live to see the success of his namesake. He died on an expedition near Shanghai in 1918. |work=[[全国公共广播电台|National Public Radio]] |date=18 February 2009 |accessdate=2009-02-20 |archive-date=2018-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616130404/https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=100778147&ft=1&f=1053 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在1908年将其以S.P.I. #23028引进了美国。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hort.purdue.edu/newcrop/morton/lemon.html |title=Lemon |publisher=Hort.purdue.edu |accessdate=2014-06-09 |archive-date=2019-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191126031859/https://www.hort.purdue.edu/newcrop/morton/lemon.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《今日医学新闻》发表一侧总结了几项研究的时事通讯，表明了这种柠檬可能对健康的一些益处，包括降低中风的风险，调节血压，预防癌症，并且高含量的维生素C可以加强免疫系统<ref name="medicalnewstoday.com">{{Cite web|title=Lemons: Benefits, nutrition, tips, and risks|url=https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/283476|website=www.medicalnewstoday.com|language=en|access-date=2020-05-06|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308133009/https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/283476|dead-url=no}}</ref>。另外果实中的植物化学物质可以帮助改善情绪，缓解焦虑和减轻体重。<ref name="Kennedy 1871–1881">{{Cite journal|last1=Kennedy|first1=D O|last2=Wake|first2=G|last3=Savelev|first3=S|last4=Tildesley|first4=N T J|last5=Perry|first5=E K|last6=Wesnes|first6=K A|last7=Scholey|first7=A B|date=2003-05-15|title=Modulation of Mood and Cognitive Performance Following Acute Administration of Single Doses of Melissa Officinalis (Lemon Balm) with Human CNS Nicotinic and Muscarinic Receptor-Binding Properties|journal=Neuropsychopharmacology|volume=28|issue=10|pages=1871–1881|doi=10.1038/sj.npp.1300230|pmid=12888775|issn=0893-133X|doi-access=free}}</ref>。

Citrus meyerii在中国通常被养在[[花盆|花盆]]中用作[[园艺植物|园艺植物]]。而在美国更为熟知用作食物，在20世纪70年代{{tsl|en|California Cuisine||加州美食}}兴起时，像是{{tsl|en|Alice Waters||爱丽丝·沃特斯}}的主厨们发掘了其中的美味<ref>{{cite news |first=Patricia |last=Lowry |title=When life hands you Meyer lemons, life is sweet |url=http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/09043/948477-34.stm |work=[[匹兹堡邮报|匹兹堡邮报]] |location=Pittsburgh |date=February 12, 2009 |quote=Meyer lemons are sweet, thin-skinned and famous for their ethereal perfume. Although common in California backyards, they are just beginning to be commercialized. Ask your friends or relatives in California to send you some," Alice Waters wrote in her ''Chez Panisse Cafe Cookbook'' in 1999.  A decade later you don't have to beg, thanks in part to Waters' championing of the Meyer and to more growers entering commercial production. |accessdate=2020-10-28 |archive-date=2013-05-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130523084410/http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/sectionfront/life/when-life-hands-you-meyer-lemons-life-is-sweet-329592/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slowfoodusa.org/index.php/programs/ark_product_detail/meyer_lemon_of_californias_central_coast/ |title=Domestic Programs |publisher=Slow Food USA |accessdate=2014-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121124232942/http://www.slowfoodusa.org/index.php/programs/ark_product_detail/meyer_lemon_of_californias_central_coast/ |archive-date=2012-11-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>，也随着[[瑪莎·史都華|瑪莎·史都華]]在她的菜谱里推荐起这种柠檬后，知名度迅速地被打响。<ref name="npr" />

== 描述 ==
[[Image:MeyerLemon.jpg|thumb]]
Citrus × meyeri成龄树高约{{convert|6|to|10|ft|m|0|abbr=on}}，不过可以被{{tsl|en|pruning||修剪}}得更小。叶片深绿色带有光泽。花朵香气扑鼻，自内往外为紫色和白色。<ref name=Floridata>{{cite web |last1=Christman |first1=Steve |title=1067 Citrus meyeri |url=https://floridata.com/Plants/Rutaceae/Citrus+meyeri/1067 |publisher=Floridata |accessdate=3 August 2018 |date=10 February 2018 |archive-date=2018-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616130125/https://floridata.com/Plants/Rutaceae/Citrus+meyeri/1067 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

果实黄色，比[[柠檬|纯正的柠檬]]更圆。<ref name=Floridata/>外果皮薄，带有香气， 在成熟时呈深黄色，略带橘色调，汁胞也呈深黄色，相较于市面常见的里斯本与尤力克柠檬，口感微甜低酸，<ref name=Floridata/>最多生有十个到二十个种子。
